Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.43,0:00:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, class.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.35,0:00:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Can anyone tell me what the decision
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.73,0:00:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,in the 1968 Stuttgart case was based upon?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.27,0:00:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well? Why is it so quiet?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.40,0:00:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this a Zen temple in the Orient?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.40,0:00:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Eimer.\NWould you like to venture a guess?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.82,0:00:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.37,0:00:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh… Well…
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.91,0:00:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Well? Can anyone break\Nthis silence for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.30,0:00:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm. I see the habitually tardy one\Nhas finally arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.56,0:00:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You're 13 minutes late.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.68,0:00:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems that your part-time pizza\Ndelivery job was quite busy today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.35,0:01:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry… Professor Kronecker.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.57,0:01:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Before you take your seat,\Nlet me ask you a question first.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.49,0:01:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have enough strength\Nto tell me what the basis was
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.11,0:01:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,for the decision in the Stuttgart case?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.82,0:01:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Oh, yes…
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.33,0:01:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The defendant claimed that\Nthe kidnapping was a sham
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.83,0:01:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and that the victim's death\Nwas merely an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.38,0:01:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,After investigating the crime scene,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.92,0:01:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,it was found that the victim's death\Nhas indeed been accidental.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.51,0:01:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It is believed that this is why\Nthe defendant was sentenced to 15 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.64,0:01:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,as intent to kill\Nmust be proven in a murder case.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.19,0:01:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well. Take a seat, Miss Nina Fortner.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.61,0:01:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.33,0:03:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,HEIDELBERG\N(GERMANY)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.62,0:03:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You saved us, Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.50,0:03:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If no one could give him an answer,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.33,0:03:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Kronecker would probably have\Nwanted us to hand in 50-page reports.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.88,0:03:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe even 50 pages isn't enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.72,0:03:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Since we're so indebted to Nina,\NI have to treat her to something to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.26,0:03:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,How about today, Nina?\NJust the two of us…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.51,0:03:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,NINA FORTNER
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.60,0:03:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Peter. I have a club meeting today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.43,0:03:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,-What?\N-Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.65,0:03:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,She turned you down again, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.44,0:03:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,How many times is that now?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.61,0:03:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.03,0:03:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to see if anyone can\Nget Nina to agree to a date.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.67,0:04:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh! I give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.76,0:04:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no! If I'm late with the deliveries,\Nthe manager will get mad at me again!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.77,0:04:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm home. I'm hungry!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.90,0:04:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodness.\NThe neighbor can probably hear you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.36,0:04:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unbecoming for your age.\NWash your hands, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.20,0:04:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.45,0:04:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, did you color your hair?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.83,0:04:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't it look good?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.00,0:04:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe she dyed her hair\Nso bright at her age.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.25,0:04:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, don't say that. She looks lovely!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.51,0:04:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not like she's going\Non a parade or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.88,0:05:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it great that mom can\Nalways stay young?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.05,0:05:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.18,0:05:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, speaking of parades…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.56,0:05:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw the kids in their costumes today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.35,0:05:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, the costume parade\Nfor St. Adrian Festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.69,0:05:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I had dressed up in those costumes\Nwhen I was little.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.65,0:05:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They were so cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.66,0:05:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You did dress up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.16,0:05:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.08,0:05:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah. You did.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.71,0:05:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.67,0:05:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see… Here…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.34,0:05:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, there it is. It's this one!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.30,0:05:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.55,0:05:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You were so happy\Nand you had so much fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.89,0:05:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.89,0:05:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm? Yes, you did.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.66,0:06:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Costume parade…?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.54,0:06:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,"A distant spring."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.87,0:06:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,"I forlornly wait for a spring that\Nwill never come… Hannah."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.42,0:06:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Hannah. Can you get over\Nyour broken heart already?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.39,0:06:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,"Allow me to send you the world's\Nmost beautiful flowers."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.35,0:06:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,"I was born to blanket you in flowers."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.40,0:06:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow. I wonder who sent me this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.11,0:06:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I see! Good for you, Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.99,0:06:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,How have you been, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.57,0:06:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been feeling well, Dr. Geitel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.45,0:06:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad to hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.12,0:06:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I could tell from the look on your face\Nwhen you came in
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.42,0:06:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the counseling room that\Nyou were doing well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.21,0:07:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you stopped having that dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.05,0:07:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The dream with a monster\Nfrom the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.76,0:07:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.14,0:07:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been sleeping so soundly\Nthat I haven't been dreaming at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.35,0:07:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know why I was so plagued\Nby such a dream night after night.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.02,0:07:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's common for people to feel insecure\Nwhen they're students.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.98,0:07:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Dreams of the future get confused\Nwith other worries,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.73,0:07:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,so you start to feel lost\Nabout who you really are.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.90,0:07:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,However, even after living a whole life,\Nit's hard to tell who you really are.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.28,0:07:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,All you can do is spend your life\Nwanting to know,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.41,0:07:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and just focus on what you can\Ndo now for your future.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.29,0:07:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I will!\NI hope to become a public prosecutor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.30,0:07:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.21,0:07:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright. That's it for today's session.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.26,0:07:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.80,0:07:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.06,0:07:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina Fortner is such a cheerful girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.02,0:08:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I can't help but feel that
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.86,0:08:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,her cheerfulness is a reaction to\Nsomething she's running away from.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.99,0:08:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Some kind of immense darkness…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.95,0:08:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.12,0:08:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't pretend you didn't know, Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.87,0:08:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.83,0:08:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,"I was born to blanket you in flowers."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.67,0:08:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I never thought you had\Nsuch excellent literary skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.09,0:08:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know anything about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.01,0:08:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you turned me upside down,\Nwords like those would never fall out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.80,0:08:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.89,0:08:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I only gave my email address\Nto my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.18,0:08:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.56,0:08:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.98,0:08:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All I know is\NI have yet another romantic rival.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.24,0:08:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder who it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.41,0:08:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,In this brutal murder case in Munich,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.91,0:08:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the perpetrator first killed\Nthe parents with a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.42,0:09:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, he strangled the two children\Nwith a rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.46,0:09:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,From the court records,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.88,0:09:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,can anyone explain the judge's ruling?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.13,0:09:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Nina Fortner?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.26,0:09:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you not understand the question?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.64,0:09:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,No… Uh… The trial was focused on
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.61,0:09:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the cold-blooded murder\Nof the whole family…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.65,0:09:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,-Huh?\N-The evidence…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.95,0:09:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The evidence…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.16,0:09:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh. There are times you\Ncan't answer either, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.71,0:09:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.13,0:09:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.72,0:09:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.30,0:09:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you alright?\NDo you want to go to the infirmary?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.10,0:10:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I… I'm fine. I just felt a little faint.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.64,0:10:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,After listening to the professor…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.40,0:10:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What?\NAbout the brutal massacre of the family?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.90,0:10:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.99,0:10:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you were quite a tough person,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.12,0:10:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're a lot more sensitive\Nthan I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.75,0:10:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you watch terrifying horror films\Nwhen you were little?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.62,0:10:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.92,0:10:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The counselor, Dr. Geitel, would say this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.25,0:10:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,"If you trace it back, it'll be simple."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.13,0:10:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,"Let's try to remember\Nsome of your childhood."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.55,0:10:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,-I…\N-Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.64,0:10:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have any memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.39,0:10:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember anything\Nbefore the age of ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.79,0:11:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,My memories… 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.08,0:11:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,My childhood memories…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.80,0:11:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,COLOGNE\N(GERMANY)
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.31,0:11:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Both of them were very nice people.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.94,0:11:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe the way they were killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.23,0:11:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The children?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.11,0:11:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I think there was a boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.94,0:11:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe his name was Michael.\NThey lived together for two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.28,0:11:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,A boy? Was there a boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.41,0:11:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, called Michael, I think.\NHe was about 14 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.29,0:11:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Michael? I guess there was\Nsomeone like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.55,0:11:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you asking?\NAre you the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.55,0:11:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Michael Reichmann.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.64,0:12:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He was in my class.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.18,0:12:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,However, he didn't have\Nmuch of a presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.02,0:12:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a little embarrassed,\Nbut I don't remember much about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.06,0:12:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't even know if he had any friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.82,0:12:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, there was no record\Nabout him, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.94,0:12:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a fire six years ago,\Nand it burnt everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.79,0:12:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Six years ago in Cologne,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.79,0:12:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,a young man called Michael was here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.62,0:12:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And Michael's real name is…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.54,0:12:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,"Johan"… I guess I used to have that name.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.47,0:12:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.26,0:12:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But what's the use of knowing that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.14,0:12:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I only know he's a twin\Nand has committed many murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.10,0:12:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.32,0:12:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What am I doing…?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.41,0:13:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Twin… What about the sister?\NWhere is his sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.66,0:13:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,"I will come for you soon."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.66,0:13:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.37,0:13:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Saying that he will come for me soon…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.71,0:13:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.17,0:13:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,A child? Yes, I think it was\Nseven or eight years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.05,0:13:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So Mr. and Mrs. Heinau, who were killed,\Nwere fostering a boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.64,0:13:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What was he like?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.73,0:13:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,"What was he like"?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.40,0:13:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It was such a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.69,0:13:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And he only lived with them\Nfor about a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.65,0:13:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.90,0:13:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he have a younger sister with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.16,0:13:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It was only a boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.66,0:13:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I want to forget about what\Nhappened to the couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.45,0:13:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I even thought about moving away\Nafter what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.13,0:14:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I know about that boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.47,0:14:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on up. I was about to have some tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.40,0:14:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Please have a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.61,0:14:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.86,0:14:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, I am--
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.61,0:14:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.22,0:14:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Have some tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.72,0:14:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh… Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.53,0:15:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a doctor, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.99,0:15:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The boy told me about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.86,0:15:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You're Dr. Tenma, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.66,0:15:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,He's coming for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.45,0:15:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.62,0:15:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.79,0:15:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The email was anonymous.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.83,0:15:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You look so happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.09,0:15:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't be thinking\Na Prince Charming on a white horse
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.67,0:15:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,will be coming for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.47,0:15:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you jealous?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.55,0:15:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You're daydreaming again, Nina.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.93,0:15:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,"I was born to blanket you in flowers."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.48,0:15:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There aren't any guys\Nwho talk like that these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.61,0:15:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Have you noticed\Na strange guy in our class recently?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.24,0:15:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.61,0:15:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That famous seat in Room 12,\Nwhere you're bound to be called on.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.24,0:15:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The guy just sat there calmly,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.83,0:15:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,but he never got called on\Nby the professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.37,0:15:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! And did you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.58,0:15:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,During the class, he kept staring at Nina.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.42,0:16:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,-Huh?\N-That's him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.17,0:16:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.63,0:16:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What else?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.09,0:16:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The Prince Charming!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.51,0:16:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That boy was highly grateful to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.39,0:16:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.39,0:16:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that you saved his life and you\Nmeant more to him than his parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.81,0:16:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What name did he call himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.36,0:16:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Franz…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.82,0:16:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But he said it wasn't his real name.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.65,0:16:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He told you about himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.53,0:16:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,so he trusted you that much?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.83,0:16:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Franz, who showed out of nowhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.96,0:16:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,was taken in by Mr. and Mrs. Heinau\Nwho lived in the flat across the hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.71,0:16:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He was with them for a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.34,0:16:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,No, actually. It was 14 months
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.68,0:16:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,from March 1987 to April 1988.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.35,0:16:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Then one day, he just disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.98,0:17:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He was very bright and well-mannered.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.40,0:17:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he come to this room?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.98,0:17:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.53,0:17:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I live alone,\Nso I always welcomed him here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.03,0:17:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He would sit in that chair\Nand study diligently.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.33,0:17:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I taught him English and French,\Nand he mastered them in a flash.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.79,0:17:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Before he disappeared,\Nhe was fluent in both languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.76,0:17:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He was only 12 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.80,0:17:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you recall anything else about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.81,0:17:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He listened to my stories attentively.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.64,0:17:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What stories do you think he was\Nmost interested in?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.07,0:17:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The war stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.07,0:17:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The war?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.90,0:17:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,During World War II,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.07,0:17:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I was on the crew of a U-boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.28,0:17:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,His favorite story was
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.66,0:18:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,about the time we were attacked\Nby one of the Allies' destroyers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.42,0:18:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We were attacked by the enemy\Nat a depth of 120 meters,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.04,0:18:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but we kept going\Neven after we suffered a fatal blow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.09,0:18:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The vessel was creaking under\Nthe pressure, and we all waited in terror.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.60,0:18:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We returned from that living hell\N38 hours later.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.10,0:18:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Ordinary children would listen\Nto it as a story of adventure.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.86,0:18:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But he was different.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.86,0:18:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He was mostly interested in…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.45,0:18:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the terror.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.95,0:18:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The extreme terror.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.29,0:18:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the reaction of a person\Nstanding on the edge of death?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.37,0:18:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That boy was only interested in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.71,0:18:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He took pleasure in terror.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.92,0:18:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh… What kind of expression did he have\Nwhile he was listening to your stories?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.97,0:19:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably with a gleam in his eyes,\Nand a smile on his face.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.52,0:19:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.06,0:19:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, I'm blind.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.15,0:19:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I don't know that boy's real name,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.74,0:19:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and I don't even know what he looked like.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.36,0:19:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Earlier, you said that he trusted me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.91,0:19:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, he doesn't trust anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.37,0:19:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,There is only one person he trusts.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.17,0:19:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It was his sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.50,0:19:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, I… I'm looking for that sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.88,0:19:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He said he would go to collect her\Nwhen she was 20 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.14,0:19:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Go where?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.55,0:19:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,To Heidelberg.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.10,0:19:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm heading out!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.31,0:19:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Ride your scooter safely!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.52,0:19:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.82,0:19:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.36,0:19:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.16,0:19:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.08,0:20:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's… time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.58,0:20:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.63,0:20:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't we decide already?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.34,0:20:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We would tell her on her 20th birthday…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.76,0:20:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that she's not our child.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.31,0:20:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait. I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.10,0:20:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?\NDidn't you want to meet him?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.69,0:20:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We told him to come here
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.15,0:20:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and meet you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.82,0:20:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Good luck with your Prince Charming.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.82,0:20:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,See you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.82,0:20:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Clara! Beate!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.95,0:20:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe they did this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.05,0:20:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hey, look!\N-He's coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.39,0:21:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Hel… Hello. Are you Ms. Nina Fortner?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.40,0:21:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Ye… Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.48,0:21:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Um… My name is Otto Hubermann.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.94,0:21:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh… Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.01,0:21:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Who…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.72,0:21:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.72,0:21:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I've seen him… somewhere… before.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.74,0:22:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Who… are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.59,0:22:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.05,0:22:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,-Nina!\N-Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.63,0:22:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,-Nina!\N-What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.92,0:22:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?\NAre you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.34,0:22:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina! Wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.43,0:22:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,-Nina!\N-Are you alright?
